{"TopicId":191573,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Kerbal Space Program 1.9: \u0022There\u2019s No Place Like Home\u201D Grand Discussion Thread","CreatedByName":"UomoCapra","CreatedById":167737,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-12T11:19:00Z","PageNum":10,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-06T13:49:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223752592\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583502263\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184845\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MechBFP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, MechBFP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHence, set your altitude higher when using the set position cheat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t need it, I just tell.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, as this happens to the runway, it should also happen to any building like \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThen what altitude should one set not to fall down from the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E height missing for a meter?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe, the developers would check an object presense at the selected coordinates and add its height to the menu altitude.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-06T13:54:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClearly you do need it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-06T14:49:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223752594\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583502589\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe, the developers would check an object presense at the selected coordinates and add its height to the menu altitude.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s the difference between closing an Issue and implementing a feature:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIssue #xxxxx : \u0022implement a cheat allowing the user to arbitrarily reposition a landed craft on the PQS map\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFeature : implement a cheat allowing the user to safely move the craft to anyplace on the current planet without exploding the damned thing, by checking for obstacles and objects and preventing spawning the craft inside any existing collider.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Developer did his job properly, the issue was closed. The QA team did their job properly, the issue was implemented as specified.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Product Owner (or whatever they call the guy calling the shots there), on the other hand, failed while writing the requirements and specifing the task.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-06T20:31:47Z\u0022 title=\u002203/06/2020 08:31  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 6, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Lisias\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Etyops. as usulla.\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-06T14:52:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t complain, I just tell what I\u0027ve seen and how I understand it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HansonKerman","CreatedById":185809,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T11:48:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223739909\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581538300\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022185823\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JebIsDeadBaby\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/12/2020 at 3:11 PM, JebIsDeadBaby said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, next stop KSP 2.0? \u003Cspan\u003E:-)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Elmao, they\u2019ll probably pull a Minecraft and jump into 1.10\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T11:52:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223755020\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583927310\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022185809\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HansonKerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, HansonKerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Elmao, they\u2019ll probably pull a Minecraft and jump into 1.10\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s actually development standard, and has been discussed and explained to death \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T15:03:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223755020\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583927310\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022185809\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HansonKerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, HansonKerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Elmao, they\u2019ll probably pull a Minecraft and jump into 1.10\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223755024\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583927536\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Curveball Anders\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Curveball Anders said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s actually development standard, and has been discussed and explained to death \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe a visual would help to drive the point home.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Version_history\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Version_history\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022TjDhlk4.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002251.79\u0022 height=\u0022463\u0022 width=\u0022894\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/TjDhlk4.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"greenfox24","CreatedById":203259,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T18:35:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndoes anyone know when it coming to enhanced edition because I know that more updated are coming to console.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Eleven","CreatedById":60502,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-15T21:25:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI might be a little late to the 1.9 party....I\u0027m running 1.9.1 and my old 1.8.1 save seems to load up just fine but when I try to switch to some landed vehicles on Laythe,\u00A0several things with wheels fly\u00A0into the air and gets destroyed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot everything tho. I have a plane and a tanker with wheels, they get destroyed every time I load into that area. I also have a \u0027base\u0027 with some\u00A0hitchhiker pods that has wheels but it\u0027s unaffected. Also there\u0027s an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E lander without wheels that loads up just fine. But if I try and load any vehicle in that area (they are all in close proximity), the plane and the tanker fly into the air and get destroyed.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn a side note I have a similar setup landed on Minmus, an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E on wheels and it loads up just fine.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there maybe some global setting I can change to affect wheeled vehicles to tone down whatever is causing this crazy bounce upon loading?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(EDIT) image added to show the setup, this is from my 1.8.1 game save:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022hZBqqAn.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/hZBqqAn.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-15T21:40:15Z\u0022 title=\u002203/15/2020 09:40  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 15, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Eleven\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Etypos and added image\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Manul","CreatedById":189366,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-17T04:01:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223757154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221584307517\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002260502\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Eleven\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/16/2020 at 12:25 AM, Eleven said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there maybe some global setting I can change to affect wheeled vehicles to tone down whatever is causing this crazy bounce upon loading?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can use PhysicsRangeExtender, it fixes bounce when enabled.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nP.S. My ground constructions placed on Laythe shore 30m from the water in 1.7.3 got spawned in the water in 1.9 and exploded.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-17T04:04:18Z\u0022 title=\u002203/17/2020 04:04  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 17, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Manul\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"stefsilver","CreatedById":181078,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-18T04:40:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nman i just cant wait till they give us full Gemini and Soyuz parts\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lewie","CreatedById":203745,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-11T19:54:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u2019m bummed cus I play enhanced edition on PS4 and I\u2019m not even playing with 1.8 moar boosters! Yet. I can\u2019t wait to get 1.8 and 1.9 updates!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hebzepbiah Kerman","CreatedById":203770,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-17T20:46:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Dessert airfield looks amazing with 1.9!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hebzepbiah Kerman","CreatedById":203770,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-18T16:17:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI actually never knew that the RE-M3 Mainsail was supposed to be the Ariane 5 Vulcain until this update. Nice revamps.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-20T13:41:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223772764\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587226628\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022203770\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hebzepbiah Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/18/2020 at 5:17 PM, Hebzepbiah Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI actually never knew that the RE-M3 Mainsail was supposed to be the Ariane 5 Vulcain until this update. Nice revamps.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt was just meant to be a generic engine until it was revamped actually.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hebzepbiah Kerman","CreatedById":203770,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-20T15:38:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223773503\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587390094\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183830\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RealKerbal3x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, RealKerbal3x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt was just meant to be a generic engine until it was revamped actually.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh... thought so.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lewie","CreatedById":203745,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-26T22:06:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen will console get this update...I know they said sometime in July. Don\u2019t get me wrong, I really do appreciate that...but a set date would be nice. Preferably sooner then later...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}